name: Ming-Na Wen
description:
A commission of @Zorglub.

Ming-Na Wen is an American actress of Chinese descent, known for her roles in many movies and different TV shows, including The Mandalorian and The Book of Boba Fett.

This TI trained really fast, and I ended up selecting step 600 as the best one out of the handful I tested. As usual, it was trained on a dataset of 18 images and with my standard settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (m1ngnawen-600:0.99), a woman, RAW, close portrait photo, bodysuit with zipper, cleavage, fishnet stockings, pale skin, slim body, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6"
